appendParam

public static final java.lang.String appendParam(java.lang.String url,
                                                 java.lang.String param,
                                                 java.lang.String value)
                                          throws java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException
Helper function to append a new parameter to an existing URL.
Handles the cases:
  • when the URL doesn't have any query parameters;
  • when the URL already has query parameters;

Parameters:
url - The original URL
param - The name of the parameter to be added in the URL
value - The value of the parameter to be added in the URL
Returns:
The processed URL.
Throws:
java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException - Thrown when illegal characters are detected.
